[2] OIE notification
Date: Mon 6 Aug 2007
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), Disease
Information 2007; 20(32) [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/wahid-prod/public.php?page=single_report&pop=1&reportid=5869>

Foot and mouth disease, United Kingdom
--------------------------------------
Information received on (and dated) 4 Aug 2007 from Dr Debby Reynolds,
director general and chief veterinary officer, Department for Environment,
Food and Rural Affairs (DEFRA), director general for animal health and
welfare, London, United Kingdom
Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Start date: 29 Jul 2007
Date of confirmation of event: 3 Aug 2007
Report date: 4 Aug 2007
Date submitted to OIE: 6 Aug 2007
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: September 2001
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: foot-and-mouth disease virus, serotype O
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (basic)
Report pertains to: entire country
New outbreaks
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak location: England (fields in Normandy Surrey, Normandy, Surrey)
Total animals affected
Species: cattle
Susceptible: 64
Cases: 38
Deaths: 0
Destroyed: 64
Slaughtered: 0
Outbreak statistics
Species: cattle
Apparent morbidity rate: 59 per cent
Apparent mortality rate: 0 per cent
Apparent case fatality rate: 0 per cent
Proportion susceptible removed*: 100 per cent
* Removed from the susceptible population either through death,
destruction, or slaughter
Epidemiology
Source of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: a total of 64 cattle are kept on a premises with
a home farm (with 4 cattle) and 2 fields (38 and 22 respectively). Clinical
signs were only present in some of the 38 cattle kept on one of the 2
fields. All 64 cattle were killed and rendered.
One outbreak has been confirmed. An epidemiological investigation is under
way. It is not possible to declare this event resolved until that
investigation is completed.
Control measures
Measures already applied
- movement control inside the country
- screening
- disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s)
- quarantine
- stamping out
- zoning
- vaccination permitted [this statement should be clarified. - Mod.AS]
- no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: none specified
Diagnostic test results:
Laboratory name and type: IAH Pirbright, United Kingdom (OIE's Reference
Laboratory)
Species: cattle
Test: reverse transcription-polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR)
Test date: 3 Aug 2007
Result: positive
Species: cattle
Test: antigen (Ag) detection ELISA (enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay)
Test date: 3 Aug 2007
Result: positive
--
